Fibrate drugs market is segmented based on product, application, and distribution channel. The product segmentation includes fenofibrate, gemfibrozil, clofibrate, and others. Fenofibrate is anticipated to have a significant market share due to its effectiveness in lowering cholesterol and triglyceride levels. The application segment comprises hyperlipidemia, cardiovascular disease, and others. With the increasing prevalence of cardiovascular diseases globally, the cardiovascular disease segment is expected to dominate the market. In terms of distribution channel, the market is categorized into hospital pharmacies, retail pharmacies, and online pharmacies. The retail pharmacies segment is likely to witness substantial growth attributed to the ease of accessibility and availability of a wide range of fibrate drugs.

